{[%evp 0,27,49,27,29,10,13,23,23,9,25,25,25,12,37,-5,19,23,43,5,19,19,22,21,20,
11,21,14,10,6]} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. Nc3 Be7 5. cxd5 exd5 6. Bf4 Bf5
7. h3 O-O {the starting point of this chapter. Black spends no time on pawn
moves and finishes the development. We have to be slightly careful here.} 8. e3
$5 {a very rare case where we start with e3.} (8. g4 {here runs into} Be4 9. e3
c5 $132) 8... Nbd7 9. g4 {the right time.} Bg6 {is met with the thematic} (9...
Be6 {is comfortably met with the thematic} 10. Bd3 c5 11. O-O $14 {[%csl Re6]
[%cal Gf3g5,Ga1c1,Gd3b1] with a typical strategic advantage due to the
inactive bishop on e6 and the weaknesses on c5/d5.}) (9... Be4 {can be met with
} 10. g5 {[%csl Re4] where black faces issues with the bishop.} Ne8 11. Bd3 $1
({another possibility is} 11. Nxe4 dxe4 12. Nd2 Bxg5 13. Bxg5 Qxg5 14. Nxe4 {
but black has a better version of the ...c6 lines as he has not spent time on
it yet, and can attack our knight with ...Ndf6 next.}) 11... Bxd3 12. Qxd3 {
[%cal Ge1c1,Gh3h4]} c6 13. h4 Bd6 14. O-O-O $14 {White retains great attacking
prospects on the kingside.}) 10. Nh4 {with the intention to win the bishop.}
Be4 (10... Bb4 11. Nxg6 hxg6 12. Qb3 {gives us exactly the position we were
looking for.} Qe7 13. Bg2 c6 14. a3 $14) (10... Re8 11. Nxg6 hxg6 12. Qb3 $14 {
[%csl Rb7,Rd5][%cal Gf1e2,Ye1c1,Gh3h4] is also quite comfortable for us.}) 11.
Rg1 $1 {[%cal Gg4g5,Yc3e4] a strong move. We want to push the knight back with
g5 and only then capture on e4.} c6 ({trying to strike in the center with} 
11... c5 {is met with} 12. g5 cxd4 13. exd4 Ne8 14. f3 Bg6 15. Nxd5 $14 {
where white keeps an edge due to the extra pawn.}) 12. g5 Ne8 13. Qg4 {[%cal
Ge1c1] a good prophylactic move. We anticipate Bd6 and prepare 0-0-0.} (13. f3
Bg6 $132 {[%csl Re7,Gf4][%cal Ge7d6]}) 13... Bd6 ({trying to stop us from
castling on the queenside with} 13... Bb4 {is met with} 14. f3 Bg6 15. Kf2 $14)
14. f3 Bg6 15. Nxg6 hxg6 16. Bd3 $14 Bxf4 17. Qxf4 $14 {[%cal Ge1f2,Gh3h4,
Gh4h5] the difference here, is that our pawn structure is intact. We will place
our king on f2 next, and try to blast open the kingside with h4-h5 next.} *

