15. Bd3 Bd6 {[%csl Rh2][%cal Gd6e5]} 16. Qe2 {getting out of the pin} (16.
O-O-O {runs into} Qf8 {[%cal Yf8c5,Gd6e5]}) 16... Qh4 (16... Qg5 {is
comfortably met with} 17. O-O {[%cal Ge4e5,Gf2f4]}) 17. g3 Qh3 18. O-O-O $14)
12. gxf3 Nxd5 {and here I recommend going for the rarer} 13. h4 $5 {which
stops Qh4. h4 is also useful in a subsequent kingside attack.} (13. O-O-O Nxc3
(13... a5 $5) 14. Bxc3 Qh4 $11 {is quite fine for black.}) {we will be
